  "description": [
    "15STALESRATIFY CHILD LABOR 0 Nine to Take Action in 1933 Have Certified to State Department Br the Associated Press All the States that ratified the child labor amendment at the last sessions of their Legislatures have now certi fied to the State Department bring ing the legal listing up to the full 15 The 1933 ratifications totaled nine Michigan North Dakota Ohio Oregon Washington New Hampshire New Jer sey Illinois and Oklahoma Previously six States had ratified Arkansas 1924 Arizona California and Wisconsin 1925 Montana 1927 Colo rado 1931 The 1933 ratifications totaling more than in the entire previous eight years that the amendment had been pending In the State Legislatures were at tributed by labor leaders who have con sistently urged the legislation to a changed public opinion They hold that the ratification action by the States has arisen from a new be lief that child labor is not economi cally profitable With the further impetus given to ruling out child labor In recovery codes the labor leaders predict further ratifications are likely when Legislatures reconvene Some argument has arisen as to Whther ar not the child labor amend ment was lost as a result of adverse action in"
